= Extracted Lists
<extracted-lists>
The list environments below are extracted from arXiv LaTeX source and
wrapped for pdfLaTeX validation.

+ Positions of the nearly marginal thermal operators in the Kac table of
  a unitary minimal model #mi(`M_p`) for #mi(`p \gg 1`). The operators
  #mi(`\phi_{(n,n+2)}`) are relevant, while the operators
  #mi(`\phi_{(n,n-2)}`) and #mi(`\tilde \phi_{(n,n)}`) are irrelevant.

+ Special solutions of the RG equations in the vicinity of
  #mi(`M_{p,p-1}`) (schematic). (a) A trajectory in #mi(`{\cal R}_p`).
  (b) A trajectory in #mi(`{\cal C}_{p-1}`). (c) A redundant trajectory.

+ Self-conjugate trajectories in the vicinity of the fixed point
  #mi(`M_p`) (schematic). (a) A trajectory in #mi(`M_{p+1,p-1}`). (b) A
  self-similar trajectory.

+ The #mi(`C`)-function #mi(`C(\tau,\tau_0)`) of the unique self-similar
  trajectory #mi(`\check u_{p}^i(\tau,s(\tau_0))`): a step in the
  staircase pattern for #mi(`\tau_0
  = 3.2`), #mi(`3.6`), #mi(`4.0`) and #mi(`4.4`) (solid lines). For
  larger values of #mi(`\tau_0`), the steps get more pronounced as the
  solutions tend towards the limit trajectory #mi(`M_{p,p-1}`)
  (long-dashed line).

+ \(a) The RG flow in the vicinity of #mi(`M_p`). A self-similar
  trajectory of regime 1 (solid line) visits all fixed points,
  trajectories in regime 2 or 3 (long-dashed lines) visit two fixed
  points, and a trajectory in regime 4 (short-dashed line) visits only
  one fixed point. (b) The resulting phase diagram in the
  #mi(`(t_{p}, \bar t_{p})`)-plane.
